#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.45"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.45:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:0.2"
msgid "5. Dhammikavagga "
msgstr "5. About Dhammika "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.45:0.3"
msgid "45. Iṇasutta "
msgstr "45. Debt "

# NOTE: Alternative title: “The Buddha predicts the history of late capitalism.”
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: Dāliddiyaṃ → dāḷiddiyaṃ (bj) | daḷiddiyaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.45:1.1"
msgid "“Dāliddiyaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, isn’t poverty suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual pleasures?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:1.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (1) "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.352, sc2
#. VAR: daliddo → daḷiddo (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: anāḷhiko → anāḷhiyo (bj) | anāḷiko (si, pts1) | anaddhiko (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an6.45:2.1"
msgid "“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko iṇaṃ ādiyati, iṇādānampi, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti? "
msgstr "“When a poor, penniless person falls into debt, isn’t being in debt also suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual pleasures?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:2.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (2) "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an6.45:3.1"
msgid "“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko iṇaṃ ādiyitvā vaḍḍhiṃ paṭissuṇāti, vaḍḍhipi, bhikkhave, dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti? "
msgstr "“When a poor person who has fallen into debt agrees to pay interest, isn’t the interest also suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual pleasures?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:3.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (3) "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: kālābhataṃ → kālagataṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:4.1"
msgid "“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko vaḍḍhiṃ paṭissuṇitvā kālābhataṃ vaḍḍhiṃ na deti, codentipi naṃ; "
msgstr "“When a poor person who has fallen into debt and agreed to pay interest fails to pay it when it falls due, they get a warning. "

msgctxt "an6.45:4.2"
msgid "codanāpi, bhikkhave, dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti? "
msgstr "Isn’t being warned suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual pleasures?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:4.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (4) "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an6.45:5.1"
msgid "“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko codiyamāno na deti, anucarantipi naṃ; "
msgstr "“When a poor person fails to pay after getting a warning, they’re prosecuted. "

msgctxt "an6.45:5.2"
msgid "anucariyāpi, bhikkhave, dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti? "
msgstr "Isn’t being prosecuted suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual pleasures?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:5.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (5) "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an6.45:6.1"
msgid "“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko anucariyamāno na deti, bandhantipi naṃ; "
msgstr "“When a poor person fails to pay after being prosecuted, they’re imprisoned. "

msgctxt "an6.45:6.2"
msgid "bandhanampi, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti? "
msgstr "Isn’t being imprisoned suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual pleasures?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:6.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (6) "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an6.45:7.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dāliddiyampi dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, iṇādānampi dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, vaḍḍhipi dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, codanāpi dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, anucariyāpi dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, bandhanampi dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino; "
msgstr "“So mendicants, poverty, debt, interest, warnings, prosecution, and imprisonment are suffering in the world for those who enjoy sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "an6.45:7.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci saddhā natthi kusalesu dhammesu, hirī natthi kusalesu dhammesu, ottappaṃ natthi kusalesu dhammesu, vīriyaṃ natthi kusalesu dhammesu, paññā natthi kusalesu dhammesu—"
msgstr "In the same way, whoever has no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities "

msgctxt "an6.45:7.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye daliddo assako anāḷhiko. "
msgstr "is called poor and penniless in the training of the noble one. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an6.45:8.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko saddhāya asati kusalesu dhammesu, hiriyā asati kusalesu dhammesu, ottappe asati kusalesu dhammesu, vīriye asati kusalesu dhammesu, paññāya asati kusalesu dhammesu, kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "Since they have no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, or wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities, they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an6.45:8.2"
msgid "Idamassa iṇādānasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how they’re in debt, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.353, sc9
#. VAR: paṇidahati → padahati (mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:9.1"
msgid "So tassa kāyaduccaritassa paṭicchādanahetu pāpikaṃ icchaṃ paṇidahati. "
msgstr "In order to conceal the bad things they do by way of body, speech, and mind they harbour corrupt wishes. "

# NOTE: Note the progression in these four terms.
msgctxt "an6.45:9.2"
msgid "‘Mā maṃ jaññū’ti icchati, ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti saṅkappati, ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti vācaṃ bhāsati, ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti kāyena parakkamati. So tassa vacīduccaritassa paṭicchādanahetu … pe … so tassa manoduccaritassa paṭicchādanahetu … pe … ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti kāyena parakkamati. "
msgstr "They wish, plan, speak, and act with the thought: ‘May no-one find me out!’ "

msgctxt "an6.45:9.3"
msgid "Idamassa vaḍḍhiyā vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how they pay interest, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an6.45:10.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ pesalā sabrahmacārī evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "Good-hearted spiritual companions say this about them: "

msgctxt "an6.45:10.2"
msgid "‘ayañca so āyasmā evaṅkārī evaṃsamācāro’ti. "
msgstr "‘This venerable acts like this, and behaves like that.’ "

msgctxt "an6.45:10.3"
msgid "Idamassa codanāya vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how they’re warned, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an6.45:11.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ araññagataṃ vā rukkhamūlagataṃ vā suññāgāragataṃ vā vippaṭisārasahagatā pāpakā akusalavitakkā samudācaranti. "
msgstr "When they go to a wilderness, the root of a tree, or an empty hut, they’re beset by remorseful, unskillful thoughts. "

msgctxt "an6.45:11.2"
msgid "Idamassa anucariyāya vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how they’re prosecuted, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an6.45:12.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā nirayabandhane vā bajjhati tiracchānayonibandhane vā. "
msgstr "That poor, penniless person has done bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re trapped in the prison of hell or the animal realm. "

#. VAR: evaṃkaṭukaṃ → evaṃdukkhaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:12.2"
msgid "Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekabandhanampi samanupassāmi evaṃdāruṇaṃ evaṃkaṭukaṃ evaṃantarāyakaraṃ anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya, yathayidaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayabandhanaṃ vā tiracchānayonibandhanaṃ vāti. "
msgstr "I don’t see a single prison that’s as brutal, as vicious, and such an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary as the prison of hell or the animal realm. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an6.45:13.1"
msgid "Dāliddiyaṃ dukkhaṃ loke, "
msgstr "Poverty is said to be suffering in the world, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:13.2"
msgid "iṇādānañca vuccati; "
msgstr "and so is being in debt. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:13.3"
msgid "Daliddo iṇamādāya, "
msgstr "A poor person who has fallen in debt "

# NOTE: I interpret this line a little differently to BB.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:13.4"
msgid "bhuñjamāno vihaññati. "
msgstr "worries even when spending the loan. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an6.45:14.1"
msgid "Tato anucaranti naṃ, "
msgstr "And then they’re prosecuted, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:14.2"
msgid "bandhanampi nigacchati; "
msgstr "or even thrown in jail. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:14.3"
msgid "Etañhi bandhanaṃ dukkhaṃ, "
msgstr "Such imprisonment is true suffering "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:14.4"
msgid "kāmalābhābhijappinaṃ. "
msgstr "for someone who prays for pleasure and possessions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.354, sc15
msgctxt "an6.45:15.1"
msgid "Tatheva ariyavinaye, "
msgstr "In the same way, in the noble one’s training "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:15.2"
msgid "saddhā yassa na vijjati; "
msgstr "whoever has no faith, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:15.3"
msgid "Ahirīko anottappī, "
msgstr "no conscience or prudence, "

# NOTE: BB has no note, but the reading is obscure to me. PTS reads “vinicchaya”. Comm. “Pāpakammavinibbayoti pāpakammavaḍḍhako”, probably echoing the line a little further down. MA 125 has 作惡不善行 “do bad unskillful deeds”. Thanissaro translates “contemplating evil actions” which seems to fit the main text better.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:15.4"
msgid "pāpakammavinibbayo. "
msgstr "contemplates bad deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an6.45:16.1"
msgid "Kāyaduccaritaṃ katvā, "
msgstr "After doing bad things "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:16.2"
msgid "vacīduccaritāni ca; "
msgstr "by way of body, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:16.3"
msgid "Manoduccaritaṃ katvā, "
msgstr "speech, and mind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:16.4"
msgid "‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti icchati. "
msgstr "they wish, ‘May no-one find me out!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
#. VAR: saṃsappati → saṅkappati (mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:17.1"
msgid "So saṃsappati kāyena, "
msgstr "Their behavior is creepy "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:17.2"
msgid "vācāya uda cetasā; "
msgstr "by body, speech, and mind. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:17.3"
msgid "Pāpakammaṃ pavaḍḍhento, "
msgstr "They pile up bad deeds "

# NOTE: This is an idiom. Compare Thag 2.32.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:17.4"
msgid "tattha tattha punappunaṃ. "
msgstr "on and on, life after life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an6.45:18.1"
msgid "So pāpakammo dummedho, "
msgstr "That stupid evildoer, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:18.2"
msgid "jānaṃ dukkaṭamattano; "
msgstr "knowing their own misdeeds, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:18.3"
msgid "Daliddo iṇamādāya, "
msgstr "is a poor person who has fallen in debt, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:18.4"
msgid "bhuñjamāno vihaññati. "
msgstr "and worries even when spending the loan. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an6.45:19.1"
msgid "Tato anucaranti naṃ, "
msgstr "And when in village or wilderness "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:19.2"
msgid "saṅkappā mānasā dukhā; "
msgstr "they’re prosecuted "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:19.3"
msgid "Gāme vā yadi vāraññe, "
msgstr "by painful mental plans, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:19.4"
msgid "yassa vippaṭisārajā. "
msgstr "which are born of remorse. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an6.45:20.1"
msgid "So pāpakammo dummedho, "
msgstr "That stupid evildoer, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:20.2"
msgid "jānaṃ dukkaṭamattano; "
msgstr "knowing their own misdeeds, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:20.3"
msgid "Yonimaññataraṃ gantvā, "
msgstr "goes to one of the animal realms, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:20.4"
msgid "niraye vāpi bajjhati. "
msgstr "or is trapped in hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "an6.45:21.1"
msgid "Etañhi bandhanaṃ dukkhaṃ, "
msgstr "Such imprisonment is true suffering, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:21.2"
msgid "yamhā dhīro pamuccati; "
msgstr "from which a wise one is released. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:21.3"
msgid "Dhammaladdhehi bhogehi, "
msgstr "With confident heart, they give "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:21.4"
msgid "dadaṃ cittaṃ pasādayaṃ. "
msgstr "with wealth that is properly earned. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "an6.45:22.1"
msgid "Ubhayattha kaṭaggāho, "
msgstr "That faithful householder "

# NOTE: gharamesin = Skt gṛhamedhin = householder
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.2"
msgid "saddhassa gharamesino; "
msgstr "wins both ways: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.3"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammahitatthāya, "
msgstr "welfare and benefit in this life, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.4"
msgid "samparāyasukhāya ca; "
msgstr "and happiness in the next. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.5"
msgid "Evametaṃ gahaṭṭhānaṃ, "
msgstr "This is how, for a householder, "

# NOTE: See BB’s note.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.6"
msgid "cāgo puññaṃ pavaḍḍhati. "
msgstr "merit grows by generosity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "an6.45:23.1"
msgid "Tatheva ariyavinaye, "
msgstr "In the same way, in the noble one’s training, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:23.2"
msgid "saddhā yassa patiṭṭhitā; "
msgstr "whoever is grounded in faith, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:23.3"
msgid "Hirīmano ca ottappī, "
msgstr "with conscience and prudence, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:23.4"
msgid "paññavā sīlasaṃvuto. "
msgstr "wise, and ethically restrained, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "an6.45:24.1"
msgid "Eso kho ariyavinaye, "
msgstr "is said to live happily "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:24.2"
msgid "‘sukhajīvī’ti vuccati; "
msgstr "in the noble one’s training. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:24.3"
msgid "Nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ laddhā, "
msgstr "After gaining spiritual bliss, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:24.4"
msgid "upekkhaṃ adhitiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "they concentrate on equanimity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "an6.45:25.1"
msgid "Pañca nīvaraṇe hitvā, "
msgstr "They give up the five hindrances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:25.2"
msgid "niccaṃ āraddhavīriyo; "
msgstr "constantly energetic, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:25.3"
msgid "Jhānāni upasampajja, "
msgstr "and enter the absorptions, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:25.4"
msgid "ekodi nipako sato. "
msgstr "unified, alert, and mindful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "an6.45:26.1"
msgid "Evaṃ ñatvā yathābhūtaṃ, "
msgstr "Truly knowing in this way "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:26.2"
msgid "sabbasaṃyojanakkhaye; "
msgstr "the end of all fetters, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:26.3"
msgid "Sabbaso anupādāya, "
msgstr "by not grasping in any way, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:26.4"
msgid "sammā cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "their mind is rightly freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "an6.45:27.1"
msgid "Tassa sammā vimuttassa, "
msgstr "To that poised one, rightly freed "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:27.2"
msgid "ñāṇañce hoti tādino; "
msgstr "with the end of the fetters of rebirth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:27.3"
msgid "‘Akuppā me vimuttī’ti, "
msgstr "the knowledge comes: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:27.4"
msgid "bhavasaṃyojanakkhaye. "
msgstr "‘My freedom is unshakable.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "an6.45:28.1"
msgid "Etaṃ kho paramaṃ ñāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "This is the ultimate knowledge. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:28.2"
msgid "etaṃ sukhamanuttaraṃ; "
msgstr "This is the supreme happiness. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:28.3"
msgid "Asokaṃ virajaṃ khemaṃ, "
msgstr "Sorrowless, stainless, secure: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:28.4"
msgid "etaṃ ānaṇyamuttaman”ti. "
msgstr "this is the highest freedom from debt.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.45:28.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

